      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NUGGET ROGERS (2) has come from this barrier to miss by narrow margins as runner-up in the last two outings, using the sprint lane to finish just a head from the winner in second at Echuca last week. That was a higher-graded race than this and a nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Could take this out. PISTOL PEARCE (3) should find this easier than when fifth here last start. Led from this barrier and dug deep to win at Geelong prior so may be hard to catch. ANGELS WATCHING (9) is on the radar after a fair effort from this row in a better race last start and a Bendigo win three back. KING SAINT (6) may need luck from a wider draw but won at this circuit and distance earlier in the campaign.",
